<BaseLayout
  title="About — Vincent Del Toral"
  description="About Vincent Del Toral — software engineer with 7 years of experience, now consulting directly with businesses."
>
  <section class="section section-narrow">
    <div class="reveal">
      <h1 style="font-size: 2.4rem; margin-bottom: 32px;">About</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="about-content reveal" data-delay="100">
      <p>I've spent seven years as a software engineer — backend systems, full-stack apps, the whole range. I worked on teams building products that people actually used, and I got good at taking messy requirements and turning them into clean, working software.</p>

      <p>What I love about this work is building things you can point to — software that directly saves money, brings in revenue, or eliminates hours of manual work every week. Tangible problems receiving concrete solutions. That's the stuff I find most rewarding.</p>

      <p>Most of the people I work with aren't technical, and that's totally fine. I'm happy to hop on a call, talk through what's going on in your business, and help you figure out what makes sense to build. No pressure or jargon, just an honest conversation about your options.</p>

      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get In Touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
